sentences: Ian Cooper (born 14 August 1970) is an Australian violinist.
Cooper began learning the violin at age 4 from his mother Jan Cooper, a Suzuki Violin teacher.
In 1990, Cooper was mentored by the French Jazz Violinist Stéphane Grappelli.
After performing with the guitarist Tommy Emmanuel at his invitation at the Sydney Opera House in 1992, Cooper joined Emmanuel on tour until 1997.
After performing with the guitarist Tommy Emmanuel at his invitation at the Sydney Opera House in 1992, Cooper joined Emmanuel on tour until 1997.
Cooper has also been a member of trumpeter James Morrison's sextet since 2007.
Cooper's main violin was made by E.H. Roth in Markneukirchen, Germany in 1926 and is modelled on an Antonio Stradivari 1714 Cremona instrument.
